besiege /bɪˈsiːdʒ/

(besieging,besieged,besieges) 

1. V-T If you are besieged by people, many people want something from you and continually bother you. 不断打扰 [usu passive] 

例： She was besieged by the press and the public. 她不断被媒体和公众打扰。 

2. V-T If soldiers besiege a place, they surround it and wait for the people in it to stop fighting or resisting. 围攻 

例： The main part of the army moved to Sevastopol to besiege the town. 这支部队的主力前往塞瓦斯托波尔去围攻那个小镇。

